.TH "fc_remove_host" 9 "fc_remove_host" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fc_remove_host \- called to terminate any fc_transport-related elements for a scsi host.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" fc_remove_host
.BI "(struct Scsi_Host *shost "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "shost" 12
Which \fIScsi_Host\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is expected to be called immediately preceding the
a driver's call to \fBscsi_remove_host\fP.

WARNING: A driver utilizing the fc_transport, which fails to call
this routine prior to \fBscsi_remove_host\fP, will leave dangling
objects in /sys/class/fc_remote_ports. Access to any of these
objects can result in a system crash !!!
.SH "NOTES"
This routine assumes no locks are held on entry.
